This paper deals with ranking forestry journals based on citation data, which falls under the domain of information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG). The use of Google Scholar and ISI Web of Science also suggests a focus on digital libraries (DL). Additionally, the paper may touch upon cybersecurity (CY) and cryptography (CR) as it discusses the use of objective ranking methods.
